/*!
    \page gltfViewer.html
    \title gltfViewer
    \ingroup tools

    \brief The gltfViewer is a tools that allows to preview glTF2 files
    rendered with the Kuesa Qt 3D engine.

    \image gltfViewer.jpg

    \section1 Usage

    It is a command line application on all platforms except macOS.

    \badcode
    Usage: tools/gltfViewer/gltfViewer [options] source
    \endcode

    This tool renders glTF 2.0 files.

    \section2 Example:
    \badcode
    ./gltfViewer [-f] my_file.gltf
    \endcode

    \section2 Options:
    \list
    \li -h, --help               Displays this help.
    \li -v, --version            Displays version information.
    \li -f, --fullScreen         show full screen.
    \li -p, --play <animations>  play named animation
    \li -l, --loop               loop animations
    \li -c, --camera <camera>    use named camera
    \li -s, --scene <scene>      index of the glTF scene to load
    \endlist

    \section2: Arguments:
    \list
    \li source                   gltf 2.0 file to render.
    \endlist

    \section2 Runtime Keyboard Shotcuts:
    \list
    \li space       Toggle play state of animations
    \li tab         Render the scene with the next camera
    \li previous    Render the scene with the previous camera
    \li ctrl + r    Reload the glTF file
    \endlist
*/
